  "time_ut": 1660752034,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d85\u0db1\u0dca\u0db1\u0dcf\u0dc3\u0dd2 \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0dc5\u0db3\u0db4\u0ddc\u0dc5\u0dad\u0dca \u0dc4\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc3\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dd2 - \u0d9c\u0dd9\u0da9\u0dd2\u0dba\u0d9a\u0dca 700 \u0d89\u0d9a\u0dca\u0db8\u0dc0\u0dba\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The pineapple market is also booming - more than 700 per fruit",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Growers and traders point out that due to the situation where it is not possible to grow pineapples, they have had to leave the country, trade and export pineapples and because of this thousands of people are losing their livelihood.",
        "Due to the bad situation, there are about 70 shops in Ballummahara and Imbulgoda, which used to be sleepy towns for pineapple trade in Gampaha district along the Colombo-Kandy road.",
        "It is said that Nawala area was popular for pineapples in the past, but later pineapple cultivation was done very successfully mostly in Gampaha district, but at present this cultivation has become impossible. The prices of pineapples have gone up so much that there is no sale.",
        "In this regard, it was revealed that the lack of fertilizers and oils used for pineapple cultivation is the main reason for the fall in yields.",
        "Retailers say that due to the current shortage of pineapple, the price of a kilo is around 250 to 300 rupees and a pineapple that was sold at a price of 200 rupees has to be sold at a price exceeding 700 rupees.",
        "A spokesman of a company that exported pineapples to several countries on a large scale stated that due to the shortage of pineapples and the increase in prices, the export of pineapples that earned foreign exchange to the country has been completely stopped and the government should take steps to provide solutions to the existing bad situation."
      ],
